<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.001 Vargas, Getulio/134⅔</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the Under Secretary of State</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-08">January 8, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I merely told Martins that if I went to the West Indies this Winter I
                            hoped much President Vargas could meet me in some central location like
                            Trinidad. Nothing further.</p>
                        <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>